<br>
Personally, I'd rather they do full fledged expansions than &quot;extensions.&quot;<br>
<br>
I'd gladly pay 29.99, at stores or directly to SoE, for a 15-zone expansion with additional features.  That has never been a question, because otherwise I'd not be here.<br>
<br>
Paying 17.99 for a five-zone expansion is, IMO, a rip-off, even more so because SoE offered this product DIRECTLY over the net, which meant that they completely bypassed the money distributors like Best Buy/EBGames typically takes.  In essence, SoE not only charged MORE for this expansion and offered less content overall, but they also reaped more of the profit.<br>
<br>
I don't like this and I really don't like seeing the addicted mass all handing over their wallets like it was nothing.  A little bit at a time is how these things get expensive, people.  If a business knows they can charge higher, they will.  Sooner than you know SoE would be offering &quot;extensions&quot; every two monthes - five zones, maybe even four, for $18.  I know that at that point, there will be people who think &quot;Hey, 18 bucks, no big deal, that's just like going to the movies twice.  I can handle that.&quot; And those people will drive the prices even higher, never realizing that they are just helping SOE min/max their profits by offering the least amount of content for the most amount of money.<br>
<br>
Whatever happened to those freely offered zones and revamps? Have you noticed that SoE has been leaving more and more broken content unfixed while plodding ahead with &quot;extensions&quot;? Where's my revamped Acrylia? Where's the revamped VP VI said they'd make? Where's the revamped Droga they started doing? Where's the new zone/content every 2-3 monthes that used to be the case? <br>
<br>
Replaced - all replaced - by things like PoP and LoY.  don't get me wrong, I like LoY and the new zones more than anything I saw in PoP, but that only serves to prove my point.  <br>
<br>
SoE has found that they can 1) charge 29.99 for an expansion with the majority of the content meant for less than 10% of EQ's population and 2) charge 17.99 for an expansion that's essentially 5 new zones + a new race + some interface improvements and &quot;utilities&quot; for EQ.<br>
<br>
